1611:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h **** /**
1612:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   * @brief  Set Address of the USART node.
1613:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   * @note   This is used in multiprocessor communication during Mute mode or Stop mode,
1614:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         for wake up with address mark detection.
1615:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   * @note   4bits address node is used when 4-bit Address Detection is selected in ADDM7.
1616:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         (b7-b4 should be set to 0)
1617:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         8bits address node is used when 7-bit Address Detection is selected in ADDM7.
1618:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         (This is used in multiprocessor communication during Mute mode or Stop mode,
1619:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         for wake up with 7-bit address mark detection.
1620:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         The MSB of the character sent by the transmitter should be equal to 1.
1621:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         It may also be used for character detection during normal reception,
1622:Drivers/STM32G0xx_HAL_Driver/Inc/stm32g0xx_ll_usart.h ****   *         Mute mode inactive (for example, end of block detection in ModBus protocol).
